# 3. Development Environment Setup

Follow the steps below to configure your local environment.

---

## Required Software

Install the following tools:

- Node.js (v18 or later)
- Docker
- Git
- VS Code or preferred IDE
- PostgreSQL
- Postman or API client

Verify installation:

node -v
npm -v
git --version
docker --version


---

## Cloning the Repository

Clone the main project repository.

git clone https://github.com/jano-agri/jano-platform-api.git

cd jano-platform-api

Install dependencies:

npm install

---

## Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the root directory.

Example configuration:

PORT=4000
DATABASE_URL=postgres://localhost:5432/jano_dev
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key


Do not commit `.env` files to the repository.

---

## Running the Application Locally

Start the development server:

npm run dev

The API will run on:

http://localhost:4000


---

## Running Tests

Run automated tests using:

npm test

Expected output:

All tests passed


Tests must pass before submitting pull requests.

